She is famous for jealously guarding her privacy, favouring a small wedding to a lavish celebrity ceremony and taking her grandmother s maiden name to shield her family from the limelight. But Natalie Portman said portraying grief-stricken Jacqueline Kennedy had taught her the virtue of celebrities giving more of themselves to the public. Jackie, Chilean filmmaker Pablo Larrain s first English-language feature, is a searing and intimate portrait of the first lady in the week after John F Kennedy s assassination in 1963. Portman told journalists at the American Film Institute s AFI Fest in Los Angeles, how she admired the stoic and dignified face Jackie put on for the public after her tragedy